cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY 

The paper discusses issues related to Natural Language Processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on Target Dependent Sentiment Analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses learning methods and the complexity of language models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the lack of comparability and generalisability in train, test or validation data, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the need for documentation and code release, which could place it in cs.CY (Computers and Society).
